name: Eglinton Park Community Center
directions: First floor, near the front desk.
comment: Has all- gender changing stall, bathrooms, and showers, with access to the indoor pool. However, you can't go through it to the outside pool.

name: Neshama Park
directions: Next to the playground, in a small, shed-looking building.
comment: The bathroom is closes early in the evening, but is open all day.

name: Norfolk Public Library Family Restroom
directions: Towards the back of the library, near the children's section. Sort of tucked in a corner by the windows facing Henningson Foods

name: Circle K
directions: back corner

name: Kwik Tripp
directions: In the back near the Men's room

name: Ca va
comment: Sign says Gender Neutral Bathroom

name: Five Bellow
directions: Back of the store

name: Lucky’s Coffee Roasters
directions: Straight back to the left once you enter location

name: Grand Central Brewhouse
comment: Three Gender neutral bathrooms, single stall, not locked

name: Boomerang Park Stalls
directions: Top of the park, multiple unisex stalls

name: Starbucks
directions: First entry on the right has two bathrooms.
comment: Really busy but there are some nice mugs you can pretend to look at while you wait and in line. The bathroom doors are transparent but too foggy from the outside to see inside. The sink in the left room just dribbles slightly which makes it impossible to wash you hands. Honestly pretty sucky…

name: Homage
directions: In an unmarked room/closet behind the counter.
comment: You will need to ask to use it. Owner and staff are trans-friendly.

name: Starbucks Coffee
directions: Go downstairs to the additional seating downstairs. At the bottom of the stairs turn right. The bathroom is through the door in front of you.
comment: You have to be a paying customer.

name: My Neighborhood US Storage Centers
directions: On the 2nd floor- follow signs for office and restrooms
comment: One unisex stall. It is a 2-3 minute windy walk after getting off elevators. Also accessible from office entrance of storage unit

name: Willard-Diloreto Hall
directions: Second floor from campus side turn right or first floor street side turn left
comment: Must have a CCSU ID card to access the building in the evening

name: Mullins Cheese Retail Store
directions: Two single occupancy unisex restrooms just right of the entrance

name: Commerce Building
directions: Commerce building, turn left down the hallway, follow the passage up a few steps, turn left, pass the lockers and the bathroom entrance is the unmarked white door on the right
comment: Uct student card is often required to access the building

name: Transgender Center of the Rockies
directions: Enter Mile High Behavioral Healthcare building, enter Transgender Center of the Rockies (first door on the right)
comment: We’re a trans community center! Come check out our resources!

name: The Trailhead / Loppet Foundation
directions: Just inside the entrance - left when you enter then down the hall on the right
comment: Open to public

name: Center on Halsted
directions: Second floor, take a right out of the elevators and you'll see it on the right.
comment: This is an LGBTQ+ community center, free to come and go!

name: Suburu Stadium
directions: Family restrooms concourse sections 124, 106, 331 and 313
comment: For Philadelphia Union and other events. Requires ticket for admission.

name: Ain't Normal Cafe
directions: Single restroom with toilet to the right of cashier.
comment: I always get coffee, so maybe just for customers?

name: St. George’s Episcopal Church
comment: Single unisex, accessible bathroom available for anyone attending a service, event, or meeting at the church (does not have to be a church-sponsored event or meeting).

name: Atrium 2nd floor
directions: Second floor, down a hallway to the left of the Plant Wall, on the right side of the hall. Right next to a Men's washroom.
comment: Will have to go up one flight of stairs or use the elevator, feels like you're entering office space.

name: Cape May County Zoo: Safari Cafe
directions: There are 3 Gender Neutral / single stall bathrooms by the indoor seating area

name: Lamplighter Brewing - CX
directions: All restrooms are single stall, gender neutral. There are two floors and each has 3 restrooms plus 1 accessible restroom. There’s an elevator to the second floor.

name: University Community Center (UCC)
directions: Main floor towards the back of the building across from Starbucks
comment: Originally used to be mens on left and womens on right but now anyone can use either side.

name: Sunflower Bakehouse
directions: By the back entrance
comment: Two single bathrooms marked unisex. Sign on door says “whatever” . I don’t recall if they are accessible bathrooms.

name: The Bearded Monk
directions: Two gender-neutral bathrooms near the bar.
comment: This business location is a transgender safe space.

name: Ozone's Brewhouse
comment: Two gender neutral restrooms

name: Briggs Taphouse
directions: At the back of the restaurant. 2 Gender Neutral Bathrooms

name: Erik's DeliCafe
comment: Two spacious unisex bathrooms. Clean.

name: Subway
directions: Right in the front entrance to the right

name: Susquehanna Orchards
directions: Park in front of the barn and walk to the back of the building with the garage door
comment: Free period products

name: Flour Bakery & Cafe
directions: There is a code for the door, but just ask the counter staff and they will give it to you.

name: Bagelshere
comment: Restroom for paying customers only

name: Coffee Landing
directions: back room

name: Jack in the box
directions: In the back of the restaurant.

name: Echo Park Lake Park
comment: Restrooms in the park are mostly gender neutral.

name: The 320 Market Cafe
directions: Back left of building behind bar.
comment: You do not have to get anything at the bar, just walk back or ask.

name: Linfield University Pioneer Hall
directions: In Pioneer Hall underneath the steps on first floor and second floor

name: Redmond Municipal Airport
directions: From front entrance to airport, head right. Single stall family restroom.

name: Meridian Travel Center
directions: Look to the left just after going in the main doors. Middle bathroom is the single occupancy any gender bathroom.

name: The Compound
directions: a single restroom is located at the top of the stairs, back hall. very private and safe
comment: LGBTQIA safe space- help yourself to the restroom

name: Home Depot
directions: Right between the gendered toilets.
comment: Single seat, family lavatory with changing table.

name: Noodles and Co.
street: 29991 SW Town Center Loop E, Wilsonville, OR 97070

name: RJ's Restaurant
directions: From side door off on Monroe Street, make a right. Restrooms in back corner of restaurant
comment: 2 gender neutral handicapped accessible single restrooms. Conservative town but people are nice and will leave you alone. Restaurant closes at 2pm and closed on Wednesdays

name: Kroger
directions: On the deli side a little but past the Starbucks inside.
comment: There are gendered stalls as well as a unisex single unit bathroom that contains both a urinal and a standard toilet.

name: Costa Swinton
directions: Two gender-free cubicles. Turn right after the counter.
comment: Supposed to be a paying customer but there is no lock / code

name: Costa Prestwich
directions: One gender-neutral cubicle downstairs, past the counter on the right, and one upstairs (turn right as you come up the stairs)

name: Cumberland Farms
directions: Walk in only customer entrance, bathroom is in sectioned off room towards the back left of the store.
comment: Single unisex stall, slightly sketchy. Door handle broken but does lock.

name: Walmart
directions: Family rest room and nursery rooms in back

name: Kate's Café
directions: Middle of the café, on the left

name: Coffee #1
directions: At the back on the left

name: East Bayfield Community Center
directions: On the first floor, near the gendered washrooms.

name: Fashion Place Mall
directions: Two Family\Gender Neutral Restrooms in the Food Court and One Near Urban Outfiters

name: Hyperion Coffee
directions: All the way to the back on the right
comment: You walk right past the front counter and it’s a small place so not sure if you’d have to buy something

name: DFW Reptarium
directions: In the back (go left from the check-out counter).
comment: It is a single occupant restroom labeled Public Restroom. Staff are LGBT+ friendly as well.

name: Lake Superior College
directions: From Student Services entrance, veer left and turn left. It's set back in the kitchen between Student Services and Disability services.
comment: Accessible only when Student Services or Disability Services is open (8am to 4:30pm on weekdays). Employees only. Students allowed with employee escort.

name: Windsor Youth Centre
directions: There are two unisex washrooms on the second floor of the building(the larger washroom has a changing table).
comment: The centre is restricted to youth(29& under) so you may not be granted permission to use it if you're over the age range.

name: Nooddi
directions: Bathrooms down corridor to the left of the kitchen.
comment: Nice people, not sure if you have to order something.

name: Rei Co-op
directions: When you walk in turn left and you'll see the restrooms. The gender neutral room is left of the women's.
comment: Seemingly dog friendly.

name: Gelato Fiasco
directions: straight back
comment: paying customers only maybe??

name: All-Gender Restroom
directions: First floor, by the spiral staircase closest to the fountain

name: Busy Bean (on first floor)
directions: 1st floor of the bld. Walk across st into Busy Bean entrance, through the entry way and into the mall turn right. Gendered but private and safe.

name: Alton Town center Publix
directions: At the front of the store near check out lanes
comment: Very clean . Secure lock.

name: Front Street Provisioners
directions: In the back to the left.

name: Dallas Museum of Art
directions: Inside the Museum Offices on Level 2, off of the stairs
comment: It's inside offices to the left. Feel free to ask for help from the receptionist!

name: Center for the Arts
directions: Located on the ground floor just inside the ceramics studio.
comment: Open when the building is open.

name: Center for the Arts
directions: Northeast corner of the Center for the Arts, ground floor.
comment: Open when the building is open.

name: Pudsey Library
directions: walk through to back of building towards the right hand side

directions: Walk in at the front office take a right they are on the wall to your right

name: Cultivare
comment: Food, ehh
